summary: Headcanon: since Peter has super hearing, and florescent lights give off quiet but super high pitched sounds, Peter gets...
question: Headcanon: since Peter has super hearing, and florescent lights give off quiet but super high pitched sounds, Peter gets headaches a lot and has to ask the teacher if they can turn the lights off.
answer:
peter gets chronic migraines at school because of this, and he tries to keep them quiet but sometimes he does just keep his head down on the desk. the decathlon team cover for him.

when tony learns that the lights in the labs are too fluorescent for Peter, he has them changed out for a warm-light alternative because it’s easier and everyone’s eyes and also they were due for a change out anyway (they weren’t, but he can’t have Big Dad Feelings in public)

question: Genderbent Tony names: Tony: Tanya, Toni, Tonya,  Anthony: Antonia, Antonie, Antionette, Anthea. Also I just looked it up that Anthony means something beautiful & priceless. Which I believe is on purpose but very cute to know. LOOKING UP WHAT PETER MEANS YOU GET  “Decrease or fade gradually before coming to a end.” Now I’m suspicious on how they chose they chose the ending for Infinity War. I know Tom Holland improvised his death. Which is very good especially since they gave him a fake script.
answer:
Cont: The actual Peter name thing just means Stone. Petra is what I think for genderbent Peter. Petra Collin, a photographer also makes a bunch of beautiful feminine dreamy pictures that would make such a good mood board for any fem!Peter! I picture her with pigtails. Very cute hairstyles she uses for school & to get her hair out of the way but she doesn’t realize how badly Ms.Stark wants to use them as handle bars.

summary: Tony: is the equipment secure? Peter: check. Tony: web fluid loaded? Peter: check. Tony: did you have breakfast? Peter: what?...

Peter: check.

Tony: web fluid loaded?

Tony: did you have breakfast?

Tony: I added it because I care about you.

Peter: no, I didn’t have breakfast.

Tony: unacceptable. Look in your backpack.

Peter, pulling out a breakfast bar: hey, there’s chocolate chips in this!

Tony: yeah: I’m not an idiot. I know how to trick my son into eating his fibre.

Tony: web fluid loaded?

Peter: check.

Tony: did you have breakfast?

Peter: what? That’s not on the checklist.

Tony: I added it because I care about you.

Peter: no, I didn’t have breakfast.

Tony: unacceptable. Look in your backpack.

Peter, pulling out a breakfast bar: hey, there’s chocolate chips in this!

Tony: yeah: I’m not an idiot. I know how to trick my son into eating his fibre.
